00:13:05.840 --> 00:13:09.919
So we have our old metrics, my new, and the metrics by week.

00:13:09.919 --> 00:13:12.880
And let's call that new metrics like this.

00:13:12.880 --> 00:13:19.760
And then I can take my board and I can write to it my new metrics.

00:13:19.760 --> 00:13:22.719
So I have to say where do I want to write it to?

00:13:22.719 --> 00:13:30.640
So I want to write it to that same pin like that.

00:13:30.640 --> 00:13:32.200
And so it's writing back up.

00:13:32.200 --> 00:13:44.799
So what a pin gets you is versioned ways to write things back and forth, which I think is really super duper nice because you can always go back.

00:13:44.799 --> 00:13:48.159
You can also pin and version models themselves.

00:13:48.159 --> 00:13:51.200
It's really useful for model monitoring.

